Subject: [PATCH] I-wire-003 B3 (#1317): fail-loud canary for clinical-PDF
 winner (W4 mineru25) degradation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

PART B of B3. Make the silent docling fallback from the W4 clinical-PDF winner
(mineru25) OBSERVABLE so a future run cannot silently degrade the winner.

- tool_tracer.py: new ToolTracer.clinical_pdf_winner_status() derives a top-level
  manifest flag from the SAME pdf_extract rows the access layer already records
  (no fabrication, free per-query reset). degraded=true iff a pdf_extract row has
  requested_extractor==mineru25 AND a fallback_reason; carries the reason
  histogram + the CPU extractor that actually ran. Surfaced as manifest
  ['clinical_pdf_winner_degraded'] in attach_tool_utilization (the single hook
  before EVERY manifest write), alongside discovery_funnel. ON-only; OFF-mode
  byte-identical.
- access_bypass.py: _record now emits one grep-able [W4-CANARY]
  clinical_pdf_winner_degraded=true reason=... line on EVERY winner-degrade branch
  (no_gpu/empty/timeout/error) — the run-log surface for the manifest flag.
- Does NOT hard-fail the run: docling is a legit CPU fallback. The degradation is
  made observable + assertable (preflight sense), not fatal.
- test: 7-case offline unit test (win/4 reasons/mixed/docling-default/reset/
  attach-ON/attach-OFF). Verified PASS via direct logic run (worktree conftest
  needs gitignored output dirs absent here; logic is pure + env-free).

Faithfulness engine untouched — this is observability only (which extractor
produced the verbatim text strict_verify later grounds).

